                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>\n                                        <date>10th <add>?</add> 5611</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <date>14 March 1851</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My Dear Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">It was with no little anxiety that I daily<lb/>\n                                        looked for the arrival of our good friend <persName>Revd. Mr\n                                                  Isaacs</persName> (which took place this<lb/> day\n                                        a fortnight) both for himself as well as to obtain precise\n                                        news from you<lb/> it was shortly after on the Evening I had\n                                        an interview with him—he dined with me<lb/> on the\n                                                  <date>Tuesday</date>, and you may easily suppose\n                                        that the chief topic on both meetings<lb/> which truly\n                                        interested me was your affair. He delivered me your letter.\n                                        I am<lb/> truly mortified at your present state and\n                                        situation! <add>אחי אחי</add> my dear brother<lb/> I will\n                                        exclaim, is this the reward after 20 years labour?\n                                                  <add>בעבודת הקדש זו תורה וזו שכרה</add><lb/> I am\n                                        further wounded to find the result <del>such</del> of my\n                                        letters such, so important, strongly<lb/> argued, and indeed\n                                        such feeling ones which I addressed <persName>Mr. A.\n                                                  Hart</persName> on your<lb/> behalf <add>אמרתי\n                                                  לריק יגעתי</add>, my first one to him was with all\n                                        the <hi rend=\"underline\">dignities</hi> &amp; <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">honors</hi> of <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">Parnas</hi>,<lb/> and indeed he\n                                        must have communicated it to his colleagues &amp; friends\n                                        for on<lb/> some of my observations he says this. \"Neither\n                                        contention or schism exist or is<lb/> likely to exist in our\n                                        midst and your letter is the first intimation to myself<lb/>\n                                        and the board of managers of such an event.\" Any passage in\n                                        any part of<lb/> my correspondence you are at full liberty\n                                        to show only <hi rend=\"underline\">such passages</hi>\n                                        which<lb/> might be of advantage to you, but I solemnly\n                                        protest that in <hi rend=\"underline\">no way\n                                        whatever</hi><lb/> touching any individual such as\n                                                  <persName>Mr Morais</persName> &amp;c (as he is a\n                                        friend) and any <sic>triffling</sic><lb/> information must\n                                        be kept sacred and in no way my name mingled; trusting<lb/>\n                                        to your honor and <hi rend=\"underline\">integrity</hi> that\n                                        such passages at all times will be kept<lb/> confidentially;\n                                                  <add>סוד ה' ליראיו</add> Our friend\n                                                  <persName>Isaacs</persName> he is a truly good\n                                        &amp; honest man<lb/> I have known something of him before\n                                        his departure for <placeName>America</placeName>, but\n                                        my<lb/> intimacy was then with his brother\n                                                  <persName>David</persName>, their father was a\n                                        worthy person <add>תם וישר וירא אלקים/הולך יושר</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>ודי למבין</add>. <persName>Revd S</persName> I see is\n                                        this day absent, gone to <placeName>Holland</placeName> to\n                                        the same relative<lb/> on his return to\n                                                  <placeName>America</placeName> he will give you a\n                                        correct and precise account of our English<lb/> Jews, that\n                                        which I have <hi rend=\"underline\">pointed</hi> out to him,\n                                        and he himself has witnessed<lb/> the state of affairs; <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">flattery</hi>, <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">emptiness</hi> and similar\n                                                  <sic>saleable</sic> articles only;</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sb3xj7f/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
