              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sb3xj7f/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>that <hi rend=\"underline\">two</hi> of the three meetings were for\n                                        special purposes &amp; at which the<lb/> members refused to\n                                        allow any thing to be offered. (except for the purpose<lb/>\n                                        called) but has also spoken of me in a manner unbecoming a\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">friend</hi>,<lb/> let alone a\n                                        friend of upwards of Twenty years standing, you will<lb/>\n                                        therefore perceive that I cannot, as you say I may \"freely\n                                        communicate<lb/> with <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName> on the\n                                        subject of your letter altho he has as you\n                                        <del>say</del><lb/> remark cognizance of your intention to\n                                        write me.\" you must excuse<lb/> my long letters and in the\n                                        manner they are wrote I am awaiting your<lb/> immediate\n                                        answer to this and let me know precisely <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">how affairs stand</hi>.<lb/> no\n                                        doubt all the candidates are on the <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >look</hi> out. In prayer to God may<lb/> He be\n                                                  <add>אוהבך אשר בנפשך דורש ודובר</add> of all your\n                                        opponents <add>שלום לך ולכולנו ותמך ה' בידך יצלח</add> that\n                                        you<lb/> have been reelected in the sincere <add>הצעיר דוד\n                                                  בכמוהר\"ר רפאל מילדולה</add> wish of <add>ושלום לך\n                                                  שנית</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add> As n<add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> honor is such that I should not conceal\n                                                  <add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> thing from you, I deem it proper to send you a\n                                        correct copy of <add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> in <persName>Mr. H</persName> letter to me, at\n                                        the same time I must repeat any<lb/> part depending on your\n                                        honor you will make use of them to save you only<lb/> but\n                                        that my name be not mingled or to be made <add>?</add>—I\n                                        trust to<lb/> you on this! \"<hi rend=\"underline\">I now\n                                                  desire</hi> to state for your information that the\n                                        late<lb/> misunderstanding between <persName>Mr\n                                                  Leeser</persName> and this congregation tis\n                                        between<lb/> the <add>?</add>pass of a nut shell, and\n                                                  <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName> can only blame\n                                        himself<lb/> (not his friend or the congregation) if he now\n                                        finds that he has placed<lb/> himself by his own obstinacy\n                                        in so unenviable a position for a man<lb/> of his high\n                                        talents and learning\" I expect your reply<lb/> as soon as\n                                        possible that some good has been effected by your <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">party</hi><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sb3xj7f/canvas/p3"
